    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>June 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1879</date>
                    <salute>My dear Laura</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I must write a few words to thank you cordially for lending us your house.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> It was a most kind thought &amp; has pleased me greatly; but I know well that I do not deserve such kindness from anyone. On the other hand no one can be too kind to my dear wife, who is worth her weight in gold many times over, &amp; she was anxious that I should get some complete rest, &amp; here I cannot rest.— Your house will be a most delightful haven &amp; again I thank you truly</p>
<p>Believe me | Yours affectionately | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The Darwins stayed at Forster’s house, West Hackhurst, Abinger Hammer, near Dorking, Surrey from 28 June until 1 July 1879 (CD’s ‘Journal’ (Appendix II)).</note>     
        </div>    
        
